<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12120j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12120j">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12120j"> 120(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cook spud in my / oxter</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On les croyait aussi d&apos;ailleurs capables de gu&eacute;rir certaines maladies, entr&apos;autres la dartre par un simple attouchement, et en comptant &agrave;rebours en breton. Leur sang, disait-on, &eacute;tait noir et tellement chaud qu&apos;<mark>ils cuisaient une pomme sous leurs ais-selles</mark>. <small> Fran&ccedil;ois Cadic, <a name="NCEL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#NCEL"><cite title="source">Nouveaux contes et l&eacute;gendes de Bretagne</cite></a> (1922) 74-5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: In Breton, the descendants of lepers were designated by the name of &lsquo;Kakous&rsquo;. Their blood was held to be black and they allegedly could cook an apple under their armpits. </mm> </dd></dl>
